import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['year'])]
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.plot(data['year'], data['pop'], color='blue')
    ax.set_xlabel('Year')
    ax.set_ylabel('Population')
    ax.set_title('What is the trend of population over time?')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.show()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data[['country', 'life_expect']]
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(15, 10))
    ax.boxplot(data.groupby('country')['life_expect'].apply(list).values)
    ax.set_xticklabels(data['country'].unique(), rotation=90)
    ax.set_xlabel('Country')
    ax.set_ylabel('Life Expectancy')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of life expectancy across different countries?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data[['fertility', 'life_expect']]
    plt.scatter(data['fertility'], data['life_expect'], alpha=0.5)
    plt.xlabel('Fertility')
    plt.ylabel('Life Expectancy')
    plt.title('What is the relationship between fertility and life expectancy?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.style.use('ggplot')
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    pop_by_cluster = data.groupby('cluster')['pop'].sum().reset_index()
    plt.bar(pop_by_cluster['cluster'], pop_by_cluster['pop'], color='blue')
    plt.xlabel('Cluster')
    plt.ylabel('Population')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of population across different clusters?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
